column5: 2010 started off with my wife Anna and I having our first baby. What an amazing experience.  Eliana born Jan. 12th.     Eliana now.     Yes, it's true time goes by crazy fast. The last 8 months have gone by in a flash.  On to some fish...             Channel Cats on the Pin!       My first fish on the fly! Wish it was a 20" plus brown but I'll take it.              Now on to the fall.
Nice Variety of fish & congrats on the Young un Richard
Funny how steelheading came right after the birth of Eliana lol  Dude I want that t-shirt!!
Congratulations on being a daddy and great assortment of fish! Looking forward to the fall report!

It would be too hard to part with. So many miles put on that shirt. Since I know your Mr. Money Bags now...let's start the offer at $50 bucks. Your going to have to shed 20 pounds and get abs of steel!  Congrats on the job! I'm proud of you man.
